I placed an order on Friday 1/1/20 at around 8:00pm and an hour and a half later the food came. I paid in cash.  When I opened up the pizza, it wasn't a pan pizza as I ordered. I forgave this first error and when I grabbed one of the unevenly cut slices, tomato sauce began to pour out like soup (didn't ask for extra sauce). I then opened up the cinnamon twist that where cold, burned, and had no cinnamon/sugar on it. I called to complain and was immediately transferred to a manager who tried to justify all the errors instead of trying to rectify them. He got defensive and rude and agreed to only replace the cinnamon twist with the condition that I return the item original cinnamon twist (as if he was imply i was just trying to get free food). This was at around 9:30pm. He assured me the replacement would take 45 minutes to an hour, and the quality would be better,  but because how disrespectful he was to me in that conversation, I still made a complaint. 3hrs later and after 3 rudely handled follow up calls in between, I then decide to cancel the order. I asked for a refund that they said they already returned but I knew that would be impossible due to the fact that I paid in cash. I tried to explain that but they continued to hang up on me. I then received an incoming call tell me that I would get a refund but to no longer call that store for service because "they don't want my type of customer." I then left the comfort of my home to go there directly to get my refund, and return the food item that they told me to return to them as sort of proof that I wasn't trying to get free food, even though I have ordered dominoes many times before. I arrived around 1:30am. I asked for the managers name and I was lied to and told that they didn't know his name. Then I was told they where closed even though the door was propped wide open and the posted closing hours on the door for Fri and Sat was 3:00am. Then I recorded the interaction as proof which prompted the employee, that was lying to me, to go get his phone and to record me, as if he was the customer with the bad experience, or to scare me into leaving. Then he called the police on me, even though I didn't do anything wrong and lied telling them I was threatening him with a knife. Because I had already recorded the incident in its totality, I wasn't going to be intimidated, and stayed there while recording him make false allegations to the 911 operator. When the police responded, me and the employee that called, ended up having to go to the 67th precinct for 3hrs for him to then tell them that I in fact never threatened him and it was a miss understanding. All of this because I was dissatisfied with the service. I can with full confidence say that the treatment I received had alot to do with my race and the race of the people that they service, which is why they feel that they don't have to be respectful. And in a climate that has seen an increase in the killing of unarmed black men, was calling the police and making a false allegation on an African American male with a customer complaint appropriate? This man put my life in danger. There is little diversity on their staff which is part of the problem. I have full video of the incident. I'm just glad I didn't become a headline over a customer service complaint. I have contacted corporate and have yet to hear back. If I could give negative stars i would because they don't even deserve 1 star. I even had a delivery man deliver food to me from this same location while smoking a cigarette and letting smoke blow in my face and I am a non smoker. What is even more shocking is that after reviewing the complaints accumulated at this location, over a 5 year period, that corporate hasn't done anything to change what's happening there, and that in my opinion that is gross negligence.

Received a text advising our order would be ready in 8-10 minutes, we left the house as dominos is only 3-5 minutes away from our home. Once we arrived at Dominos the customers already in the store were in upset because one person had sat as early as 6:30pm waiting for a sandwich that they didn't receive until almost 8:00pm. It was pure chaos, people were enraged by the lack of customer service and it seemed like a number of orders were sent out for delivery instead of prioritizing the customers who waited in the store. We sat and waited for almost an hour for food that was horribly presented at 8:16pm in boxes that looked dismantled. Once the orders were checked one of the pizzas looked uncooked in the center, the other had an obscene amount of grease, and the third one had what appeared to be a white substance on the crust. Not to mention the chicken wings were done at the original pick up time almost an hour before our pizzas were completed. We were so upset with the order and overall customer service we left leaving the food at the establishment, forced to spend our money elsewhere due to the horrible customer experience we received this evening. This needs to be fixed promptly, training needs to go into affect immediately even when answering the phone! This location lacks the fundamentals of putting their customers first and etiquette. Strongly advise corporate to get involved before this location goes out of business.
